  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf \u0b8f\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The new cabinet will take office tomorrow in the presence of the new president",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "The new cabinet will be sworn in on Friday as an interim measure until an all-party government is formed. Ministers who have already been appointed will take oath tomorrow in the presence of the new President.",
        "Accordingly, the President's Media Division informed that the swearing-in ceremony of the ministers will be held at the Prime Minister's Office located at Flower Street, Colombo - 7.",
        "It is expected that Dinesh Gunawardena may be appointed as the Prime Minister this time. President Ranil Wickremesinghe has announced that he will seek the cooperation of all parties representing Parliament to form an all-party government.",
        "However, no party has announced a firm resolution on this. However, National People's Shakti leader Anurakumara Dissanayake announced at a media conference tomorrow that if an interim government is formed within a certain period of time, cooperation can be explored.",
        "Although Leader of the Opposition Sajith Premadasa did not comment on his participation in an all-party government, he posted on Twitter about the meeting with the President yesterday, \"Instead of giving a large number of ministerial posts to allow political opportunists to squander the country's national resources, the idea is to strengthen the parliamentary committee system to meet national expectations.\" I presented it to the President', he said.",
        "President Ranil Wickremesinghe, responding to the media's questions regarding the vacancy in the post of Prime Minister, said, \"The one who has the majority support in the Parliament will be Pramara. \"I cannot appoint the Prime Minister because I am the only member of my party,\" he replied. However, political analysts have stated that the power to appoint the Prime Minister is vested in the Executive President as per the Constitution."
      ],
